place_description: We are a local family owned coffee company in Fort Mill SC. We sell anything from seasonal lattes to black coffee. We sell our freshly roasted coffee beans as well as handmade pastries from Whisk & Wood (Charlotte NC) & Poppyseed Kitchen (Fort Mill SC). We started off in 2019 in our garage roasting coffee which then grew to selling at local farmers markets. Our coffee shop opened in 2023 serving the greater Fort Mill community.

This hidden gem is my all time favorite coffee shop in Fort Mill.  From the moment I step in, I am greeted by the warm and inviting atmosphere. The aroma of freshly brewed coffee instantly put a smile on my face.
The baristas at Humble Cup are not only skilled but also incredibly friendly. They made sure my order was just right, and the attention to detail truly showed in every sip. The coffee is exceptional, and I can tell that they take pride in using high-quality beans.
What sets this place apart is the cozy ambiance. It's the perfect spot to unwind, whether you're catching up with friends or enjoying some quiet time with a good book. The attention to decor and the comfortable seating make it a hidden gem in Fort Mill.
I highly recommend Humble Cup Coffee to anyone in the area. It's more than a coffee shop; it's a special place for coffee lovers and those seeking a positive and uplifting atmosphere! Hope to see you there!

Humble Cup Coffee Co. is a hidden gem in Fort Mill. It's a cozy little coffee shop with a warm and inviting atmosphere. The staff is incredibly friendly and always makes me feel welcome. They really know their coffee, and they're always happy to chat about different brewing methods or recommend a drink to suit your taste. I've tried a few of their lattes, and they're all amazing. The Matcha and homemade syrups are my favorite! They also have a great selection of pastries and other snacks, which are all fresh and delicious. I highly recommend Humble Cup Coffee Co. to anyone looking for a great cup of coffee in Fort Mill.

I really like this place and I hope the owners will read this review. Great coffee, delicious pastries, cute ambiance. My only complaint is that the whole place reeks of bleach. I noticed this as soon as I sat down, and then a few mins later an employee came out with a bottle of lysol gingerly spraying every square inch. Bleach is very toxic and many people are very sensitive to it. It's also not a great smell as you are sipping on coffee. Y'all could honestly just mix vinegar and water in a spray bottle. If that is too old school, there are companies that make much less harsh of cleaners. At the very least if you must use bleach, use it once at the end of the day. Clean does not equal sanitized. You can just wipe down with a rag throughout the day and sanitize once. Sorry for the rant but when the smell of cleaner is stronger than the smell of coffee roasting- its too much.

We used Humble Cup Coffee to cater coffee for our wedding and it was a major hit. Our venue had horses and their coffee truck is a renovated horse trailer. It was the perfect match. He even had a grooms choice and brides choice sign to show off our favorite coffee drinks. Everyone loved the unique touch that it added to our day. I definitely recommend Humble Cup Coffee for all your coffee catering needs. They are perfect for your wedding or other major events!

We bought French Roast beans at the ASC Greenway Market yesterday and somehow managed to wait until the next morning to grind and brew.   Using a French Press, coarse grind setting, 17 oz hot water, 32g coffee, and a 4 min steep time yielded 2 perfect cups.  Delicious!  We'll definitely buy again.
